%N A258075 Lower constant x that satisfies: x = Sum_{n>=1} frac(n*(1-x)) / 2^n.
%C A258075 A good approximation to this constant is 680/1533, which is correct to 39 digits.
%H A258075 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/DevilsStaircase.html">Devil's Staircase</a>.
%F A258075 This constant satisfies:
%F A258075 (1) 1 = x + Sum_{n>=1} {n*x} / 2^n, where {z} denotes the fractional part of z.
%F A258075 (2) 1 = 3*x - Sum_{n>=1} [n*x] / 2^n, where [z] denotes the integer floor of z.
%F A258075 (3) 1 = 3*x - Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/x], a "devil's staircase" sum.
%F A258075 (4) 2 = 3*x + Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/(1-x)], a "devil's staircase" sum.
%e A258075 x = 0.4435746901500326157860404435746901500325851143026...
%e A258075 where x = Sum_{n>=1} {n*(1-x)} / 2^n such that x < 1/2 and x > 0.
%e A258075 Other series involving x begin:
%e A258075 (a) 3*x-1 = 0/2 + 0/2^2 + 1/2^3 + 1/2^4 + 2/2^5 + 2/2^6 + 3/2^7 + 3/2^8 + 3/2^9 + 4/2^10 + 4/2^11 + 5/2^12 + 5/2^13 + 6/2^14 +...+ [n*x]/2^n +...
%e A258075 (b) 2-3*x = 0/2 + 1/2^2 + 1/2^3 + 2/2^4 + 2/2^5 + 3/2^6 + 3/2^7 + 4/2^8 + 5/2^9 + 5/2^10 + 6/2^11 + 6/2^12 + 7/2^13 + 7/2^14 +...+ [n*(1-x)]/2^n +...
%e A258075 (c) 3*x-1 = 1/2^2 + 1/2^4 + 1/2^6 + 1/2^9 + 1/2^11 + 1/2^13 + 1/2^15 + 1/2^18 + 1/2^20 + 1/2^22 + 1/2^24 + 1/2^27 + 1/2^29 +...+ 1/2^[n/x] +...
%e A258075 (d) 2-3*x = 1/2^1 + 1/2^3 + 1/2^5 + 1/2^7 + 1/2^8 + 1/2^10 + 1/2^12 + 1/2^14 + 1/2^16 + 1/2^17 + 1/2^19 + 1/2^21 + 1/2^23 +...+ 1/2^[n/(1-x)] +...
%e A258075 note that (c) and (d) involve Beatty sequences as exponents of 1/2.
%e A258075 The complement to this constant is A258072:
%e A258075 1-x = 0.5564253098499673842139595564253098499674148856973...
%e A258075 and possesses very similar properties.
%e A258075 The CONTINUED FRACTION of 3*x has large partial quotients:
